1- Terraform related terms
  Terraform configuration file 
    - Files written in Hashicorp configuration language (HCL), files have a .tf extension
  Working or Home directory
    - Configurations made up of one or more files saved in a directory.
    - it contains provider binaries, plan files and state files once terraform has run the configuration.
  Terraform uses declarative model
    - Declare the desired state of infra and it will be configured on azure to match the state.
  Terraform persists state and configuration is idempotent
    - Compares the new config state to state saved from previous terraform apply, if no changes to config, then it will not reapply the settings.
  
